tching the casters attempt it was making me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  so hard I was in tears.<br><br>The only problem I have ever had with the UI is the occasional time I right click on the screen to activate mouse look and end up clicking on a chat window by accident and pulling up the chat config menu. That hasn't been much of a problem since I removed chat window titles... just gotta get used to it.<br><br>I don't use the left button to move forward... haven't since the days of the original DOOM. <br><br>DFGH are the only movement keys I use...<br>d = turn left (becomes strafe left on right click and hold)<br>f = move back<br>g = move forward<br>h = turn right (becomes strafe right on right click and hold)<br><br>I never could understand the WASD method... fingers get tied up when switching from W (run forward) to S (run backward). Can't have that in FPS games.<br><br>The best configs come from just dropping your hands on the keyboard wherever they are comfortable and assigning keys accordingly. It really sucks that keyboards can't handle more than 4 simultaneous keystrokes at a time... I can think of many situations where I'd love to be holding down 4+ keys and hammering away on 2-3 more. If keyboards could do that I'd never bother to use the mouse at all. Mice cause me finger strain in the pinky of my right hand after about 8 hours of solid play... other than that I could go forever. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>Raviel Darkfyre</b><BR><table style="filter:glow(color=Red, strength=3)"><font color="black" size=2><b>Insidious Blood</b></font></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugeistschattenfaust.showPublicProfile?langua